snippet.title: Rush to rescue beached humpback calf
snippet.content: A BABY humpback whale has beached on Moreton Island, east of Brisbane. Ranger Terry Christensen said the calf, which is about 4m long, beached at Bulwer Wrecks on the northwestern side of the island, at about midday. Rangers and Marine Parks staff are keeping the whale cool and wet until the tide comes in to refloat it.
